{"word":"Samson","slug":"samson","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Samson</b> - son of Manoah, of the Judges<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=13&verse=24'>Jdg 13:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=14&verse=1'>Jdg 14:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=15&verse=7'>Jdg 15:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=20'>Jdg 16:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=30'>Jdg 16:30</a><p/>---\"A life of Contrasts\"<p/>Separated as a Nazarite<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=13&verse=5'>Jdg 13:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=17'>Jdg 16:17</a><p/>--yet tampering with evil associations<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=14&verse=1'>Jud 14:1-3</a><p/>Spiritual at times<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=13&verse=25'>Jdg 13:25</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=15&verse=14'>Jdg 15:14</a><p/>--yet under the power of carnal appetites<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=1'>Jud 16:1-4</a><p/>Childish in his plans<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=15&verse=4'>Jud 15:4</a><p/>--yet courageous in battle<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=15&verse=11'>Jud 15:11-14</a><p/>Mighty in physical strength<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=3'>Jdg 16:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=9'>Jdg 16:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=12'>Jdg 16:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=14'>Jdg 16:14</a><p/>--yet weak in resisting temptation<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=15'>Jud 16:15-17</a><p/>His sad end<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=16&verse=30'>Jud 16:30</a>"}]}